Two relatives accused of stealing medicine valued at R400 000 were granted bail in the Alexandra Magistrate s Court in Johannesburg, the Alex News reports.They will appear in court again when the police investigation is completed.The two accused a distributor at a medicines supply agency, and an ambulance assistant were granted R40 000 and R10 000 bail respectively.The two accused rented a storage facility at an undisclosed location, which the police raided after they were tipped off about suspicious activities at the facility. During the raid, the police confiscated a variety of restricted prescription medicines and drugs.The police investigation will determine the source of the medicines and the extent of the crime. Caxton News ServiceRead original story on alexnews.co.za